#X text 104 19 The object has multichannel support. If the left input has more than one channel \, it outputs the same number of channels in both outlets. If the secondary inlets have a signal with a single channel \, the single value is applied to all channels. If a secondary inlet is also a multichhanel signal \, then each channel gets its own value. Note \, however \, that the number of multichannels in secondary inlets need to match the same number of channels from the left input., f 68;
